speech.p:
asked the Secretary of State for the Colonies (1) the average weekly tonnage of groundnuts now being transported by the Nigerian railways to port;

2. what tonnage of groundnuts in Nigeria was carried over from the 1952–53 season; and at what cost in carry over charges and depreciation to the purchaser; and

3. what tonnage of groundnuts in Nigeria is to be purchased by the Nigerian Marketing Board during the 1953–54 season; and at what price.
